gov.usgs.traveltime

Class AuxTtRef

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.traveltime.AuxTtRef

  • public class AuxTtRef
extends java.lang.Object
    Auxiliary data augmenting the basic travel-times. This data is common to all models and only need be read once during the travel-time server initialization. Auxiliary data includes phase groups (needed for association in the Locator) and travel-time statistics. The statistics are used in the travel-time package for the arrival times of add-on phases (e.g., PKPpre) and in the Locator for association and phase weighting.
    Author:
    Ray Buland

      • AuxTtRef

        public AuxTtRef(boolean printGrp,
                boolean printFlg,
                boolean printRaw,
                boolean printFit)
         throws java.io.IOException
        Read and organize auxiliary data. Note that for convenience some processing is done on the travel-time statistics. This eliminates a stand alone program that processed the raw (maintainable) statistics into an intermediate form for the Locator.
        Parameters:
        printGrp - If true, print the phase groups
        printFlg - If true, print the phase flags
        printRaw - If true, print the raw statistics data
        printFit - If true, print the fit statistics data
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If opens fail
